title: Tottenham Hotspur v Gent, Europa League LIVE score | Daily Mail Online
text:
18:38 Here are all of this evening's UEFA Europa League round of 32 ties 
Four teams are already through, with Manchester United, Schalke and Krasnodar all progressing to Friday's last-16 draw following aggregate wins yesterday, while Olympiacos saw off Osmanlispor 3-0 earlier to join the trio in the hat. 18:32 Wembley has been touched up with Tottenham and Europa League branding The Wembley arch is lit up in the Spurs colours of lilywhite and blue ahead of the tie Spurs and Europa League branding features inside the ground before the round of 32 clash 18:27 Falling trees have been causing havoc to the transport system in Britain today 
But Tottenham Hotspur have arrived in good time and in good health at Wembley Stadium. Harry Kane of Tottenham Hotspur arrives fresh from scoring a hat-trick against Fulham Harry Winks will hope to fature having played in the first leg loss at Gent Michel Vorm and Mousa Dembele arrive at Wembley Stadium before the game Jan Vertonghen of Tottenham Hotspur (left) and Vincent Janssen looked in good spirits after arriving 18:20 Much of Britain has been kept on its toes by Storm Doris today 
But for Tottenham, they are still getting over the Gent whirlwind from last Thursday that leaves the north London side trailing in their Europa League tie.
